@node intro " Who's Who -- InTroDuCTioN -- "

 Sorry about the UnOriginality of the name and all, but in a way I'm sure it
does explain what this door does. Who's Who is a address database for
Daydream BBS, any user add his/her address to make it easier for other users
to get intouch with him/her . The idea is pretty nice, and it did take me a
while to fix most of the bugs, and I also wanted to rush it in as soon as
possible (I dunno why) and I guess this is it ! A door that proves to be
pretty usefull, and in a way, quite original in concept .

 Who's Who is not in any way, related to `Who's Who' on the Internet, so if
you were thinking this program would connect you to `Who's Who' on the net
and create a huge worldwide database or anything similar then you are
mistaken, this program was inteneded for BBS puposes only, and is supposed to
benifit all users of any BBS that includes this program as a door . Plain,
and simple .


@endnode

@node Install " Who's Who -- InsTaLLaTioN -- "

 You seem to be lucky as I've included an installation script with Who's Who,
this script only does one thing, simply copies the files to the DOORS:
directory, nothing more, nothing less, installing it as a door is entirely up
to you . Just make sure you put the execute CMD as :

 DOORS:Rexx %N DOORS:Who/ww.dd
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
That would suffice .

If you do not want to use the script (and why the hell shouldn't you ?) then
here's what you have to do . First make a directory in DOORS: call Who, iow,

makedir DOORS:Who

then copy all the files in the archive to that directory, still don't know ?
Well, it's :

copy #? DOORS:who

once you are done then that's it !

 If you do, by any chance, find ANY trouble installing a simple @{"Email" LINK contact} would
save you a lot .

@endnode

@node how2play " Who's Who -- HoW 2 UsE it -- "

 Using Who's Who is very darn simple, you are given 9 Selections (WOW!) Use
the commands in the standard way we all use them.

L -- Allows you to see who included his/her address .
R -- Allows you to read ALL the addresses included .
D -- Allows you to download (for free) the addresses .
I -- Allows you to include your address .
C -- Allows you to read ALL the comments by the people that included their
addresses .
Y -- Allows you to include your comment IF you've included an address .
W -- allows you to download (for free) the comments .
A -- Tells you about this door .
Q -- Displays five bunnies hopping around the screen and formats your
harddisk . ( Obviously quits )


 I tried to make this door pretty much `free' in feeling, you haven't got
many limitations, and you can enjoy everything ... However, there will be
modifications (HUGE) in the next version of Who's Who .
Check the @{"Future WW Releases" Link future} for more details .



@endnode

@node bugs " Who's Who -- KnoWn BuGs -- "

 Well, I have spent tons of hours rewriting this very simple code, in the end
I realised that none of that was neccessary, as I forgot to put ONE STUPID
QUOTATION !! Well, I hated myself for that, but the bug got fixed .

 For what I know, the code isn't that compact, a lot of it is wasted and dead
in a way . That personally, I consider a bug .. It's because I can actually
make it spend less time loading if I just had an hour's work on the final
code, but as I said, I want to get this program out ASAP .

 Sometimes (if you are EXTREMELY UNLUCKY) the computer gets bored of you and
doesn't load the program at all !! Well, it happened to me ONCE, but never
again, if it does happen to you then just restart the computer, but I doubt
it would happen .

 If ANY of the files in the archive is missing then the door will NOT work,
that could easily be fixed, and I assure you that will be fixed for the next
release ..

 That's what I managed to find so far, I haven't given it to the BETA testers
that offered their support, because I had to rush this door to the amin....


@endnode

@node future " Who's Who -- FuTuRe WW Releases -- "

 I have made a simple plan for Who's Who . It's future isn't that HUGE and I
doubt it that you'll find more than three or four newer versions, as this
door will hopefully reach the stage where it will remain `AS IS', but it will
actually get implemented in another door I'm working on .
(Check @{"Other Releases" Link other})

 The plans so far are as follows .

The mentioned bugs will be fixed with ease (I hope), a special SysOp menu
will be available for the SysOp to clear the files . There will be specific
information that you will be asked for your address, rather than you just jot
down whatever you like, that's just to make it more neat and arranged .

 The biggest thing I have to tell you all, that when this door does reach the
FINAL version, you will have to reffer to the new door I'm working on right
now, as Who's Who will be implemented in it (Check @{"Other Releases" Link other}) .


@endnode

@node ME " Who's Who -- AbouT ThE AuThoR

 Agh, this part tends to be irritating after you've created a few hundred
doors, I'm getting pretty much bored of writing about myself . Oh well, some
poeple just WANT to KNOW .

 Well, I'm sixteen right now, I'm in high school finish up my second year,
and have been producing doors for Daydream for the past few weeks or so . I
do not intend to make anything I create shareware, becuase I know that not
many peope register, but I might do similar stuff like upgrade packs for
nominal fees, nah, I'll just put them as emailwere and relieve myself .

 I'm (so far) not financially benefiting from any doors, I'm just doing this
for experiance sake, and just to say ` I LOVE THE AMIGA ' in my special way,
a way that is very simple, yet hardly do any people care about . You see,
that's what pisses me off, people just buy the Amiga for games and all, but
hardy are they productive in ANY WAY, for Mr G.O.D.'s sake, if you love the
Amiga, make use of it ! And that (for a reason) is why some users dump the
Amiga for other computers, a small fact is that if you program on a computer,
you are hardly to leave it without a proper reason .

 Anyway, back to ME now :), I've owned an Amiga for more than five years now,
started with an A500 with ˝meg chip and ˝ fast, in those days that WAS the
ULTIMATE ! Now I'd imagine how I survived with it . Now however, I've got an
A1200 with an Apollo 030 card with 4mb fast (soon to be 8) running at 25 Mhz,
with a nice cute 2.5 inch 540 MEGAbyte harddisk . I have temporary use of a
modem, and I have to use my sister's PC for the Net, now don't tell me I hate
the Amiga, or don't believe in its browsing power etc. it's just because I
don't have a modem or a surf squirell, but I DO have a browser and dialer and
the like ...

 The future of my computer is very uncertain, I will have to leave the Amiga,
in a year and a half's time, it is or that or if GateWay start making Amiga
Laptops or notepads . Because right now I live in Bahrain (Yeah, you've no
IDEA where it is, neither did Commodore), and in a yea and a half I wll be
leaving to Canada to complete my studies, and I can't take my Amiga with me
(poor me ...), so I just hope someone gets a Laptop out at an affordable
price, that'll make my day !

 Anyway, for the time being I'll just sit on my trusty Amiga and program
doors for you to enjoy ...



@EndNoDe

